\title{When does a "complementary" submodule exist?}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-19}
\taxon{puzzle}

\p{We know finite-dimensional inner product spaces have [orthogonal complements](vectsp-002F), but can we generalize this idea to generic modules? Let us make this question more precise:}

\p{Let #{R} be a ring, let #{T} be an #{R}-module, let #{N\subgroup T} be a submodule.}

\p{When does there exist an #{R}-module #{M} such that #{M\oplus N=T}?}